        i0.ɵɵtext(172, " \"Pretty Boy\" himself Jed Rowen will be joining Sarah French & Joe Knetter at Colorado Festival of Horror 2022: Funhouse! Jed will also be at our special DOUBLE-FEATURE slasher event Friday evening, Sept 9th starting at 7pm!\n");
        i0.ɵɵelement(173, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(174, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(175, " 7-9pm 2019\u2019s \u201CBlind\u201D showing in the Circus of the Damned Video Room ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(176, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(177, " 9-11pm 2021\u2019s \u201CPretty Boy\u201D ** COLORADO PREMIERE ** showing in Monster Main Events ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(178, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(179, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(180, " Jed Rowen is an award-winning actor who\u2019s always up for a convention appearance and is thrilled to be going back to Colorado to attend yet another one! The Colorado Festival of Horror will be screening some of Jed\u2019s best work, the features Blind and the most recent, Pretty Boy, in which Jed plays the title role. Along with these two horror gems, a movie that screened way back in 2007 in Denver, Zombie Farm, is coming back from the dead in yet another incarnation at COFOH, this time entitled Pandemic Undead. Some of Jed\u2019s other notable credits over the years include Sluggo in The Ghastly Love of Johnny X and Det. Ray Garton in the notorious worldwide phenomenon Amazing Bulk. He\u2019s also very proud of recent roles in Space Hunters: The Battle for Deepstar, That\u2019s A Wrap and Area 5150. ");
