        i0.ɵɵelementStart(211, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(212, "p", 12);
        i0.ɵɵtext(213, " Colorado Festival of Horror 2022: Funhouse is thrilled to announce actor/pro-wrestler/cosplayer Monique Dupree coming to our September 2022 convention! Monique will be meeting fans, signing autographs and doing professional photo ops. Newark, New Jersey native, Monique Dupree, is also known by the title Tha True Original Gata and in some circles, is referred to affectionately as The First Black Scream Queen. She was also The First Black \u201CTromette\u201D in many of Lloyd Kaufman\u2019s Troma Entertainment films. She has done independent horror films, comic-book, catalog and/or alternative modeling, local and national reality television and an occasional cross-over into mainstream television and cinema. Monique\u2019s most notable recent role was \u201CCaliban\u201D from Troma Entertainment\u2019s \u201C#Shakespeare\u2019s Shitstorm.\u201D She wears many hats including publishing, promotion, photography, internet radio, fitness, production and pro-wrestling. She tours behind the scenes and wrestles for former ECW star Tommy Dreamer in his promotion House of Hardcore as well as Impact Wrestling. Monique is also a professional Cosplayer appearing at events and conventions. The most notable cosplay to date being, Wonder Woman, Nubia, Mohawk Storm and Marie Antoinette. Monique has 10 children with her husband, author Anthony Saint Thomas. She is involved in several grass-root charities and social outreach organizations. Monique has completed upward of 100 films and television projects, inspired the creation of several comic-book heroines and consistently works and is for hire across the country and around the world. You Tube: Tha True Original Gata ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
